At William King's house she dropped against the door, her fingers still
                        clinging to the bell. She was past speaking when the doctor lifted her and
                        carried her into the office. "No; don't try to tell me what it is," he said;
                        "I'll put Jinny into the buggy, and we'll get back in a jiffy. I understand;
                        Hannah is worse." "Not . . . Hannah —"
